<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 7:59AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Areas of heavy snow over Southwest MT this morning...
Areas of heavy snow have developed over portions of Southwest MT
this morning. Some locations experiencing the heavy snow include
Ennis, Norris Hill, and locations north of Dillon.
Visibility is below a half mile a times, with snowfall rates
estimated around an inch per hour.
Those traveling along portions of Highway 287 from Three Forks to
West Yellowstone or Interstate 15 from Butte to Monida Pass should
be prepared for areas of heavy snow and poor visibility.</description>
